<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Words Ending With -LY — Scrabble Suffix Scoring Guide</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The -LY suffix is Scrabble's most abundant word-ending. With over 1,500 valid words, it transforms adjectives into adverbs (quick→quickly, brave→bravely) and provides endless bingo opportunities. The Y tile's 4-point value adds scoring punch to every -LY play, especially when landing on premium squares.</p>

<p>Mastering -LY words gives you a reliable path to 7+ letter bingos using common rack combinations that opponents often overlook.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why -LY Matters in Scrabble</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">L(1)+Y(4) base</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1,500+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid -LY words</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3–15</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter length range</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>The sheer volume of -LY words means you'll rarely be stuck without an option. Almost any adjective on your rack can become a bingo candidate by adding -LY, making this suffix your most reliable path to the 50-point bonus.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Top Scoring -LY Words</h2>

<div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
